column5: It would seem that this miracle gro stuff is what it is.LOL  We used it this year, for our potted plants. Lo and behold,we have a tomatoe plant growing and has now hatched it,s first offering.Anyone else use this stuff and had something grow that you didnt plant?  Very cool.
The seed got there by a bird or rodent. Could have been stuck to a bee.
How do ya know it's not some otherworldly thing that space guys have planted to tempt you? You could end up with a third leg or something.  JF
I have parsnips and dill growing in my flower pots with my begonias.  I didn't plant them.  The birds must have dropped them from the vegetable patch.  Pam

Miracle Gro rocks .... I use it once or twice in a season ... and the next day I can literally hear my plants growing  And yes ... if you happen to misplace a seed (or fruit pip) ... you'll be soon the proud owner of a new orchard
and that's what I told the cops I didn't  plant them it must be the miracle gro
Brian... you know that's illegal to grow
Probably soil from compost. Good stuff compost.
Nah, Miracle Gro is terrible for that.. you don't want it growing too fast!
